How can you write a function in MATLAB or Octave to find the longest palindromic substring in a given string? To find the longest palindromic substring in a given string using MATLAB or Octave, you can implement a function that iterates through each character in the string, expanding around each character to find palindromes of odd length, and then expanding to find even length palindromes. Here's a possible implementation:

```matlab
function w = longest_pal(s)
    % Function to find the longest palindromic substring
    % s: input string
    % w: longest palindromic substring

    n = length(s); % Length of the input string
    if n == 0
        w = ''; % Handle empty string
        return;
    end

    start = 1;
    max_len = 1;
    for i = 1:n
        % Check for odd length palindromes
        l = i;
        r = i;
        while l > 1 && r < n && s(l-1) == s(r)
            l = l - 1;
            r = r + 1;
        end
        if (r - l + 1) > max_len
            start = l;
            max_len = r - l + 1;
        end

        % Check for even length palindromes
        l = i;
        r = i + 1;
        while l > 1 && r < n && s(l-1) == s(r)
            l = l - 1;
            r = r + 1;
        end
        if (r - l + 1) > max_len
            start = l - 1;
            max_len = r - l + 1;
        end
    end
    w = s(start:start+max_len-1);
end
```

This function iterates through each character in the string, treating it as the center of a potential palindrome. It expands outwards from this center to check for palindromes of both odd and even lengths. The function keeps track of the longest palindrome found and returns it at the end.

