Since $80\%$ of the Science Club members are also in the Math Club, there are $0.8(15)=12$ students common to both clubs. Because $30\%$ of the students in the Math Club are also in the Science Club, there are $12\div 0.3=\boxed{40}$ students in the Math Club. [asy]
